  <title>Test Eleventy Edge querystrings</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Test Eleventy Edge querystrings</h1>
  <p>
    It appears that Eleventy Edge mishandles querystrings generated by get requests to forms where there are multiple checkboxes of the same name.
  </p>
  <h2>Expected</h2>
  <p>If all three checkboxs are selected in the form below, the URL generated by the form will be <code>?status=Open&status=Closed&status=Other</code> and each value passed to the query string should be present in the query returned from Eleventy Edge</p>
  <code>
    <pre>{
  "status": ["Open", "Closed", "Other"]
}
  </pre>
</code>

{% edge "liquid" %}
  <form action="." method="GET">
  <fieldset>
    <legend>Options (where a user might select multiple)</legend>
    {% assign statusOptions = "Open, Closed, Other" | split: ", " %}
    {% for opt in statusOptions %}
      <input type="checkbox" id="{{opt}}" value="{{opt}}" name="status">
      <label for="{{opt}}">{{opt}}</label><br/>
    {% endfor %}
  </fieldset>
    <input type="submit">
  </form>
  <h2>Result</h2>
  <p>Currently, only the last of any multiple matching querystring keys will be returned</p>
  <h3><code>eleventy.edge.query</code> gives us:</h3>
  <code>
    <pre>{{ eleventy.edge.query | json }}</pre>
  </code>
{% endedge %}

</body>
</html>
